n. * * * * * (c) *␣*␣* (4) Plans benefiting certain disaggregation populations of employees _(i) In general _(A) Single plan must be treated as separate plans. If a plan ( i.e. , a single plan within the meaning of section 414(l)) benefits employees of more than one disaggregation population, the plan must be disaggregated and treated as separate plans, each separate plan consisting of the portion of the plan benefiting the employees of each disaggregation population. See paragraph (c)(4)(ii) of this section for the definition of disaggregation population.
